Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Urelytrum digitatum

Assembly is haploid, and the genome is hexaploid. It has a haploid genome size of 4700 Mb, and has 30 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Urelytrum digitatum from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Dotplot of Urelytrum digitatum vs.Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Urelytrum digitatum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Urelytrum digitatum is a hexaploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 3 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Urelytrum digitatum

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Urelytrum digitatum along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Urelytrum digitatum is a hexaploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 3 lines, one for each subgenome.
